Interface ListCell<T>

All Superinterfaces:
Cell<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
CList.Node
public interface ListCell<T>
extends Cell<T>

An interface to a list cell.

Given a function f to create a list cell from a collection, such as CList.firstCell(), a list cell may be used as an iterator in the following form 

   for (ListCell cell = f(); cell != null; cell = cell.next())

Warning

The Cell.isValid() method is not intended for iteration as in 
   for (ListCell cell = f(); cell.isValid(); cell = cell.next())
rather, see the general contract for Cell.isValid().
